Basic Installation
------------------

    python setup.py install --prefix=/some/path

If the fortran compiler is not found automatically, this sequence should work:

    python setup.py build --fcompiler=name
    python setup.py install --prefix=/some/path

Where name can be, e.g., gnu95, ifort

Alternatively, if you don't have a fortran 95 compiler, edit this file and
comment out the line with "config.add_subpackage('cosmology')"
    ./esutil/setup.py


UPS
---
If you use ups or extended ups, you can install the ups table under
the prefix/ups directory:


    python setup.py install with_ups --prefix=/some/path

